sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112133
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Xis Int temperature sensitive expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Xis int (with native rbs) under the control of a temperature sensitive promoter. Terminator follows CDS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Madhvi Venkatesh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This part is in BBb Format. It is flanked by BamHI and BglII sites instead of XbaI and SpeI. More information about the BBb Format is available at:
BBb Standard Description Page
